'''普里奥拉森林公园'''（{{lang-en|Pureora Forest Park}}）是位于[[新西兰|新西兰]][[北島_(紐西蘭)|北岛]]的[[保护区|保护区]]，面积{{convert|adj=on|760|km2}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://data.linz.govt.nz/layer/53564-protected-areas/data/|title=Data Table - Protected Areas - LINZ Data Service|publisher={{tsl|en|Land Information New Zealand||Land Information New Zealand}}|accessdate=2017-10-18|archive-date=2017-10-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171018072034/https://data.linz.govt.nz/layer/53564-protected-areas/data/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。这片富饶的雨林里生长了丰富的千年[[罗汉松科|罗汉松]]，公园也被誉为“世界上最好的雨林之一”<ref>{{Cite web |url= http://www.newzealandnz.co.nz/forest-parks/pureora.html |title= Forest Parks: Pureora |publisher= New Zealand's Information Network |accessdate= 2020-08-26 |archive-date= 2013-09-23 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20130923021900/http://www.newzealandnz.co.nz/forest-parks/pureora.html |dead-url= yes }}</ref>。在历经一系列的抗议和{{le|坐树|Tree sitting}}活动后，普里奥拉森林公园于1978年修建完成，它是北岛最大的完整原始森林之一，由于植物和动物栖息地的多样性丰富，因而公园具有很高的保护价值。新西兰最大的[[桃柘罗汉松|桃柘罗汉松]]位于公园附近的私人土地上。

==历史==
20世纪70年代末，环保活动家{{le|斯蒂芬·金|Stephen King (conservationist)}}、雪莉·吉尔福德（Shirley Guildford）和其他人在现普里奥拉森林公园发起了反伐木的抗议活动。他们使用了一种新颖的方式——在树梢上搭建平台，坐在上面抗议森林里的伐木活动。他们的努力最终一箭三雕：公园于1978年得以建立；[[新西兰政府|新西兰政府]]更改了相关规定，以满足抗议者永久停止伐木活动的要求；成立了{{le|天然森林恢复信托基金|NZ Native Forests Restoration Trust}}，确保公园会将一些区域开发为现在的状态<ref name="Rawlings-WayAtkinson2010">{{cite book |last1=Rawlings-Way |first1=Charles |last2=Atkinson |first2=Brett |last3=Bennett |first3=Sarah |title=Lonely Planet New Zealand |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O9kxgh1WlZgC&pg=PT301 |accessdate=2011-01-01 |date=2010-10-01 |publisher=Lonely Planet |isbn=978-1-74179-473-1 |pages=301– |archive-date=2020-08-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200826092710/https://books.google.com/books?id=O9kxgh1WlZgC&pg=PT301 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Trust/><ref name="AucklandStar2010">{{cite news |title=Trees crash near totara campers as logging starts |date=1978-01-19 |newspaper={{tsl|en|Auckland Star||Auckland Star}}}}</ref><ref name="sirowaw.net.nz"/>。在吉尔福德的努力下，其中一片用当地树种恢复的林区在1988年她去世后被命名为“雪莉·吉尔福德树林”<ref name=Trust>{{cite web |url=http://www.nznfrt.org.nz/index.php?page_id=111 |publisher=NZ Native Forests Restoration Trust |title=Our history |work=nznfrt.org.nz |dead-url=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100125004104/http://www.nznfrt.org.nz/index.php?page_id=111 |archivedate=2010-01-25  }}</ref><ref name="sirowaw.net.nz">{{cite web |url=http://www.sirowaw.net.nz/trampnz/main-tramping-areas/163-pureora-forest-park |title=Pureora Forest Park |work=sirowaw.net.nz |accessdate=2011-01-01 }}{{Dead link|date=2020年8月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>。

==旅游==
野营、野餐、游泳和山地自行车（例如2013年开放的{{le|木材小路|Timber Trail}}）在公园内很受欢迎<ref name="DeptConservation">{{cite web |url=http://www.doc.govt.nz/parks-and-recreation/places-to-visit/waikato/waitomo-pureora/pureora-forest-park/activities/ |title=Mountain biking Pureora |work=doc.govt.nz |publisher=Department of Conservation |accessdate=2011-01-01 |archive-date=2011-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110318141244/http://www.doc.govt.nz/parks-and-recreation/places-to-visit/waikato/waitomo-pureora/pureora-forest-park/activities/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。自1987年以来，普里奥拉森林公园狩猎比赛吸引了大批猎人前来<ref name="HuntingCompetition">{{cite web|url=http://www.doc.govt.nz/about-doc/news/media-releases/2010/pureora-hunting-competition-2010-now-open/|title=Pureora Forest Park Hunting Competition 2010 – a roaring success!|work=doc.govt.nz|accessdate=2011-01-01|archive-date=2011-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111108211342/http://doc.govt.nz/about-doc/news/media-releases/2010/pureora-hunting-competition-2010-now-open/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

